Originally ripped by Terminal Escape, posted on July 04, 2020 Description from Terminal Escape:
I posted this one in the early days of The Escape (almost eleven years ago - am I really still doing this shit?!), but this cassette from 1987 bears revisiting. A collection of recordings from Dunville, Ontario's PROBLEM CHILDREN that includes their first demo from 1982, the What's Is All About demo from SUBTERFUGE (who had a short run during a PROBLEM CHILDREN hiatus in '83) early versions of most of the tracks on the criminally underrated The Future Of The World Belongs To Us LP. It's not everything, by any means, but it's a great collection of under the radar bangers from an under the radar band - off the rails irreverent hardcore punk. Who doesn't want that? Dummies. DON'T GIVE UP!!
https://terminalescape.blogspot.com/search?q=problem+children
